---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout 
	title="Privacy Policy | Virsa Labs"
	description="Privacy policy and data protection information for Virsa Labs' services. Learn how we collect, use, and protect your personal information."
>
	<main class="relative py-16 lg:py-20">
		<div class="container px-4 md:px-6">
			<div class="mx-auto max-w-3xl space-y-8">
				<div class="space-y-4">
					<h1 class="text-4xl font-bold tracking-tighter sm:text-5xl">Privacy Policy</h1>
					<p class="text-muted-foreground">Last updated: {new Date().toLocaleDateString()}</p>
				</div>

				<div class="prose prose-gray dark:prose-invert max-w-none space-y-8">
					<section>
						<h2>1. Introduction</h2>
						<p>
							This page ("Privacy Policy" or "Policy") provides our policies and procedures for collecting, using and disclosing your information and outlines the security measures we've put in place to protect the information that you store using Virsa Labs' services, including the services made available through this website, and any other software or services offered by Virsa Labs in connection with such services (the "Services"). By using these Services, you consent to the collection, transfer, processing, storage, disclosure and other uses of your information described in this Privacy Policy.
						</p>
					</section>

					<section>
						<h2>2. Information We Collect</h2>
						
						<h3>2.1 Personal Contact Information</h3>
						<p>
							When expressing an interest in obtaining additional information about the Services or registering to use the Services, Virsa Labs requires you to provide your personal contact information, such as your name, company name, address, phone number, and email address ("Personal Contact Information"). When purchasing the Services, we also require you to provide financial and billing information, such as billing name and address, credit card number, and the number of employees within the organization that will be using the Services ("Billing Information").
						</p>

						<h3>2.2 Data, Diagnostic & Login Information</h3>
						<p>
							Using our Services, you will be able to create, upload, store and share information such as company description, email ID, logo, photos, custom emails, user email IDs, etc. (collectively referred to as "Data"). This information will be stored and maintained on Virsa Labs' website. If you run into technical errors, we may request your permission to obtain crash reports and logging information ("Diagnostic Information"). Additionally, certain login information is maintained in a cookie stored locally on your computer to streamline the login process ("Login Information").
						</p>

						<h3>2.3 Analytics Information</h3>
						<p>
							As you navigate our website and use our Services, we may collect information through cookies and Web beacons ("Website Navigational Information"). This includes standard information from your web browser, your IP address, and your actions on our website ("Analytics Information").
						</p>
					</section>

					<section>
						<h2>3. How We Use Your Information</h2>
						<p>We use your information in the following ways:</p>
						<ul>
							<li>To develop and deliver our services</li>
							<li>To process your transactions</li>
							<li>To provide customer service and manage your account</li>
							<li>To improve our products, services, and marketing</li>
							<li>To send marketing communications (with consent)</li>
							<li>To analyze and optimize our services</li>
						</ul>
					</section>

					<section>
						<h2>4. Information Sharing & Disclosure</h2>
						<p>
							Virsa Labs does not sell, rent, or trade your private information to any third parties. We may share information with:
						</p>
						<ul>
							<li>Service providers and partners who help us deliver our services</li>
							<li>Legal authorities when required</li>
							<li>Professional advisors</li>
							<li>Business transferees in case of sale or merger</li>
						</ul>
					</section>

					<section>
						<h2>5. Data Security</h2>
						<p>
							We implement appropriate technical and organizational measures to protect your personal information. However, no method of transmission over the Internet is 100% secure.
						</p>
					</section>

					<section>
						<h2>6. Your Rights</h2>
						<p>You have the right to:</p>
						<ul>
							<li>Access your personal information</li>
							<li>Correct inaccurate data</li>
							<li>Request deletion of your data</li>
							<li>Object to processing</li>
							<li>Data portability</li>
							<li>Withdraw consent</li>
						</ul>
					</section>

					<section>
						<h2>7. California Consumer Privacy Act (CCPA)</h2>
						<p>
							Effective January 1, 2020, the California Consumer Privacy Act (CCPA) allows California residents to obtain certain information collected by businesses. If you are a California resident, you may exercise certain rights to access, restrict, or delete your personal information by contacting us.
						</p>
					</section>

					<section>
						<h2>8. Changes to Privacy Policy</h2>
						<p>
							We may update this policy periodically. We will notify you of significant changes by posting the new policy on this page and/or via email through the primary email address specified in your account. You are responsible for ensuring we have an up-to-date active and deliverable email address for you.
						</p>
					</section>

					<section>
						<h2>9. Contact Information</h2>
						<p>
							If you have any questions regarding this Privacy Policy, please contact us at:
						</p>
						<ul>
							<li>Email: team@virsalabs.io</li>
							<li>Phone: 484-591-4566</li>
							<li>Address: 3005 Brodhead Rd STE 23, Bethlehem Pa 18020</li>
						</ul>
					</section>
				</div>
			</div>
		</div>
	</main>
</Layout> 